Format compatibility
--------------------

ampaper aims for byte-exact compatibility with PaperBack 1.10
output: scans of pages produced by PaperBack 1.10 must decode
in ampaper, and ampaper's "legacy" output must decode in
PaperBack 1.10. This is the binary ground-truth check that
proves the rewrite is correct.

Forward features (improved encoders, AES-256, color schemes,
etc.) live behind explicit "ampaper format v2" mode flags so
they don't compromise legacy compatibility.
